
    THABISO Mbewane was allegedly stabbed to death by three thugs.The 34-year-old’s body was dumped in a ditch.After Thabiso’s body was found on Sunday, three men arrived at the cop shop one after the other and allegedly confessed to the crime.The dead man’s family believe it was Thabiso’s spirit that forced the killers to hand themselves over.All three suspects were arrested at Bekkersdal Police Station, in Westonaria, west of Joburg, on Monday.They are facing murder charge.Thabiso’s sister Nomsa (25), told Daily Sun: “My brother loved church and we believe his angels are helping him fight his killers“Thabiso left last Saturday to buy items for the church but he failed to return home. We were worried because he was not answering his phone.”Nomsa said the next day, people came to tell them her brother was dead and his body had been dumped in a ditch in Simunye, near Bekkersdal.“My father positively identified him. He had been stabbed. Rumour has it that he was killed at a house in Simunye and his body dragged to the ditch.”Nomsa said Thabiso had recently got a job and had big plans.“My brother was everything to me. All my siblings are dead and I’m the only one left,” she said.Police said a murder case was opened for investigation.The three suspects appeared in court on Tuesday and will make their second appearance soon.if(typeof za24_DisplayAd != "undefined") za24_DisplayAd("300x250","2");var viewReq = new Array();function vu(u) {var i=new Image();i.src=u.replace("&amp;","&");viewReq.push(i);}vu("https://securepubads.g.doubleclick.net/pcs/view?xai\x3dAKAOjsufkxru-1zqFfpxqjCez7MAynUG4vQo6POKc5TFrDzn6zO6sbN877yUTyr7sD6vAadsnviCLPZBUTXyxgxkcw3A2BLhe32h0JcyEA1vI50czErl_NXLbOz9tHArNm7VC6y9LZUXFTHACe73gOSh-YC84D3xfQMgut8oy6s1N5w77Vdk-XifB6Q3L1WIWY97HuaY6AB7H0xCXjULFoM_Z8Uvx6P1K1EKtA6m5P_gvzk2ihpKZh1CjEI3Pq770N_4dwm_-SmBZtJoIvUBdrD5eP3QKbRG3fA\x26sig\x3dCg0ArKJSzAJmMY54p7jwEAE\x26urlfix\x3d1\x26adurl\x3d")

   
